<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10447&amp;p=117432#p117432"><![CDATA[
I imagine there's enough variance in the exact figures among SMB1, SMB2 (J), SMB2:MM, SMB3, and SMW to make an eyeballed guess good enough, especially if you replicate 1-1 as a test case. <em>Mario Mania</em>, Nintendo's official guide for SMW, mentioned this variance in the &quot;history of Mario&quot; bit that preceded the Yoshi's Island map.<br /><br />In any case, Mario never moves faster than 4 pixels per frame. The engine depends on this.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sun Sep 01, 2013 7:31 pm</p><hr />
